item.title: [PI]Compiler Error - Of a different kind
item.dc:creator: @V_1_N_C_H V 1 N C H
item.description:
@V_1_N_C_H wrote:

www.sagi-x.com:

You should just use an integrated development environment such as eclipse, and I couldn’t see any reason for someone to increase the maximum number of errors shown apart from maybe you have a very large class that has a lot of refactoring to be done? Or a missing bracket but that should stand out to you, if you’ve got decent conventions (indentation).

I have an error in my playerassistant.java that gets cut off by the compiler, so I looked through it to find a missing bracket, and I can’t find it. So I will try eclipse.

EDIT: I tried Eclipse, And it is confusing the hell out of me…Someone explain how to compile with it please?
